<section id="about" class="content-section">
    <div class="about-container">
        <h2>About BSCF</h2>
        <p>Bangladesh Socio-Cultural Forum (BSCF) is an independent, non-political, and non-profit platform
            dedicated to the socio-cultural and educational development of Bangladeshi youth. We focus on
            enhancing social skills, encouraging participation in cultural activities, promoting environmental
            awareness, and fostering tolerance and personal growth.</p>
        <div class="vision-mission">
            <div class="vision">
                <h3>Our Vision</h3>
                <p>BSCF envisions a Bangladesh where youth empowerment is paramount, ensuring their active
                    participation and influential voice in national development. We advocate for a tolerant
                    nation, emphasizing empathy and respect for diverse religions, perspectives, and beliefs.
                    Our goal is to cultivate socially responsible, environmentally conscious citizens with
                    cultural proficiency and a global mindset, ready to engage with the world and contribute to
                    volunteerism, service, and long-term employment opportunities.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mission">
                <h3>Our Mission</h3>
                <p>BSCF engages youth from diverse backgrounds—villages, urban areas, grassroots, and
                    underprivileged regions—offering tangible behavioral skills, social responsibility, mental
                    health awareness, and cultural exchange opportunities. We empower youth through
                    volunteerism, fostering an environment where they emerge as non-communal, respectful,
                    humble, environmentally aware, and tolerant global citizens, advocating for good governance
                    and sustainable development.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

